    <rigor-reason>Tags include 'bff-api' + 'ai' + 'azure-search'; creates new `.cs` handler; load-bearing for legal-domain trust framing (architecture §2 P3); ADR-013/ADR-015/ADR-033 binding</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>4-G</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Author `RecallSessionFileHandler` (NEW) at `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/RecallSessionFileHandler.cs` implementing the T2+T5 `recall_session_file` tool per architecture §6.3 + §8.1 + §8.3. Six `purpose` enum values (`answer_question`, `quote`, `compare`, `summarize`, `extract_dates`, `verify`) and five `scope` values (`summary`, `relevant_sections`, `full_text`, `tables`, `citations`); `requireCitations: true` is the default (FR-30 + architecture §8.3 trust framing); returns `{ content, citations[{page, paragraph?, section?, text}], scope_truncated, truncation_reason }`. Reads `spaarke-session-files` index for section/sections mode — **NOT `spaarke-insights-index`** per architecture §5.2.1. Implements FR-30 + FR-31 (per-purpose retrieval semantics).
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in chat tool-handler authoring + Azure AI Search wrapper patterns + RAG retrieval semantics.</role>

  <goal>
    `RecallSessionFileHandler` lives at `Services/Ai/Handlers/RecallSessionFileHandler.cs` implementing `IToolHandler`. Mode dispatch per architecture §6.3: `summary` → reads `ChatSession.UploadedFiles[fileId].PrecomputedSummary` (5ms hot); `relevant_sections` → calls `RagService.SearchAsync` against `spaarke-session-files` index (filter `session_file_id = fileId`, query = `sectionQuery`, topK = 3); `full_text` → returns concatenated chunks ≤8K tokens, else summary + first 2K chars + `truncation_reason: "exceeded_8K"`. Marks file as recently-discussed via `IRecentlyDiscussedTracker` after successful recall. `requireCitations: true` default enforces citation-bearing response (architecture §2 P3). Telemetry tier-1 safe (no recall content). Unit tests cover all 6 purposes × all 5 scopes plus the `not_found` + `exceeded_8K` truncation paths.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per architecture §6.3 (recall flow), §8.1 (recall_session_file schema), §8.3 (citation enforcement model). The handler is the LOAD-BEARING tool for the legal-domain trust framing — its `requireCitations: true` default + the persona instruction injected by `TrustFrameInstructionInjector` (task 077) ensure the agent uses citations rather than quoting the precomputed (NOT authoritative) summary. Architecture §5.2.1 binds: this handler MUST use `spaarke-session-files` index NOT `spaarke-insights-index`.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/ManagePinnedContextHandler.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/RagService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/IRagService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/Chat/ChatSession.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">No new endpoint.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Auto-discovered handler; no manual DI line here.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Reads `IRagService` (BFF-internal) + T2 session storage directly. NO PublicContracts facade required for BFF-internal chat path.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Telemetry payload carries: handlerName + sessionId + fileId + purpose + scope + scope_truncated + truncation_reason + durationMs ONLY. NEVER content, citations text, query strings, summary text.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">≤+0.2 MB publish-size delta.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">SINGLE `ToolResult` return; no streaming. Memory tools are non-streaming.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture">§5.2.1 — MUST use `spaarke-session-files` (and optionally `spaarke-files-index` for matter-bound chunks); MUST NOT use `spaarke-insights-index` for chat memory.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture">§6.3 — mode dispatch matches the flow diagram (summary fast path, relevant_sections via RagService TopK=3, full_text with 8K truncation).</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture">§8.3 — `requireCitations: true` default; citation array shape includes `page, paragraph?, section?, text` keys verbatim.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture">§9.2 — `fileId` not in session returns structured `{ scope_truncated: true, truncation_reason: "not_found" }`; do NOT throw.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-30 + FR-31 — purpose enum biases retrieval; each purpose has documented semantics asserted by unit tests.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/architecture/stateful-chat-architecture.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
