    <criterion testable="true">`requireCitations` parameter has DEFAULT value `true` in the tool metadata + handler signature.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`grep -i "spaarke-insights-index"` returns ZERO matches in the new handler file (architecture §5.2.1 enforcement).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All 6 purposes × 5 scopes unit-tested; matrix passes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`not_found` returns structured payload (NOT exception); `exceeded_8K` truncation returns the documented summary + first 2K chars shape.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`IRecentlyDiscussedTracker.Mark` is called once per successful recall.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Telemetry payload carries no content/citation text — assertion against captured log events.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish delta reported; ≤+0.2 MB.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">code-review + adr-check exit 0.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    This is the LOAD-BEARING tool for legal-domain accuracy (architecture §2 P3). The `requireCitations: true` default is non-negotiable. If `IRecentlyDiscussedTracker` is not yet registered (its registration is part of task 091), add a null-safe defensive call so this task can land green; task 091 then makes it functional.
  </notes>

